il":", which is classified generally to chapter 16 (§ 1811 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1811"},"text":"section 1811 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddb6efa0f-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1203/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1203(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), redesignated par. (2) as (1) and struck out former par. (1). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The terms ‘Finance Board’ and ‘Board’ mean the Federal Housing Finance Board established under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1422a"},"text":"section 1422a of this title","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (1)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1204/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1204(8)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the Director” for “the Board”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Pars. (2) to (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1203/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1203(2)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated pars. (3) to (5) as (2) to (4), respectively. Former par. (2) redesignated (1)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1204/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1204(8)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the Director” for “the Board”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1203/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1203(2)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (6) as (5). Former par. (5) redesignated (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Pars. (6) to (9). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1203/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1203(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), redesignated pars. (7) to (9) and (12) as (6) to (9), respectively. Former par. (6) redesignated (5)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (10). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1203/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1203(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3), redesignated par. (13) as (10) and struck out former par. (10). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The term ‘Chairperson’ means the Chairperson of the Board.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (10)(A)(ii). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1211/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1211(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “$1,000,000,000” for “$500,000,000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (10)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1211/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1211(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “$1,000,000,000” for “$500,000,000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1204/10"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1204(10)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the Director” for “the Finance Board”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Pars. (11) to (13). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1203/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1203(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3), (4), added pars. (11) and (12), redesignated former pars. (12) and (13) as (9) and (10), respectively, and struck out former par. (11). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The term ‘Secretary’ means the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/102/s602/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–102, § 602(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “terms ‘Finance Board’ and ‘Board’ mean” for “term ‘Board’ means”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/102/s602/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–102, § 602(2)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3) and struck out former par. (3) which read as follows: “The term ‘State’ includes the District of Columbia, Guam, Puerto Rico, and the Virgin Islands of the United States.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (13). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/102/s602/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–102, § 602(3)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (13)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Pars. (1), (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73/s701/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73, § 701(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (1) and (2) and struck out former pars. (1) and (2) which defined “board” and “Federal Home Loan Bank”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73/s701/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73, § 701(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of par. (4) by striking out “(except when used in reference to the member of the Board)” after “ ‘member’ ”, was executed by striking out “(except when used in reference to a member of the board)” as the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73/s710/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73, § 710(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “or a nonmember borrower” after “member”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Pars. (9) to (12). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73/s701/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73, § 701(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (9) to (12) and struck out former par. (9) which read as follows: “The term ‘nonmember borrower’ i